Large seedling models for Tony & Kevin

Kathleen Stutzman

2024-01-25

Hidden below is code for importing the data set and log transforming variables. The best model (lowest AIC & using lrtest) is presented below, model fit checked, and pairwise comparison for Treatment Type.

I did create and test models without treatment type, but they always have higher AIC and worse model fit that those with (probably due to the control category…)

Variables investigated:
  • Treat_Type - treatment type
  • PIRI - pitch pine seedling count (10m2)
  • SO - shrub oak seedling count (10m2)
  • other - other seedling count (10m2)
  • BA_HA - basal area per hectare
  • BA_piri - pitch pine basal area per hectare
  • Mineral - exposed mineral soil (1m2)
  • avgLD - average leaf litter depth (1m2)
  • Veg_Total - total understory plant cover (1m2)
  • TFT - time between treatment and sampling (used as an offset)
  • Site/Plot_No - random effect of plots within sites

*Variables are log transformed (l. or _l)*

Pitch Pine Regeneration

Best large seedling pitch pine model

ls.m19 <- glmmTMB(PIRI ~ Treat_Type + avgLD_l + offset(l.TFT) + (1|Site/Plot_No),
                 data = ls.all3,
                 family = poisson)

                       type = 'pred', 
                       terms = c('avgLD_l', 'Treat_Type'),
                       axis.title = c("Average Leaf Litter Depth (log transformed)", "Total Count of Pitch Pine"),

Shrub Oak Regeneration

This includes QUIL (scrub oak) & QUPR (dwarf chinkapin oak)

Large seedling shrub oak model

  • Poisson, genpois, & compois models all fail and are underdispersed. Gaussian dispersion also fails. The student t distro seems to work …
  • Model versions suggest that total veg cover is important. However, shrub oak can often make up a significant portion of understory veg cover. So, of course shrub oak abundance increases as total veg cover increases. Therefore, it is dropped from the model for issues of collineraity.
ls.all3$BA_10m <- (ls.all3$BA_HA/1000)
ls.all3$l.BA_10m <- log(ls.all3$BA_10m + 1)

so.ls6 <- glmmTMB(Shrub_Oak ~ Treat_Type + l.other + l.BA_10m + l.Mineral + offset(l.TFT) + (1|Site/Plot_No),
                 data = ls.all3,
                 family = t_family)
summary(so.ls6)
